name: Morning Serenity
text:
A woman rides a bicycle along the path.
She rings her bell.
“Ding! Ding!”

A man jogs nearby.
He waves and says: “Good morning!”
The woman says: “Good morning!”

She stops to look at the lake.
The man stops too.

Man says: “The water is so calm.”
Woman says: “Yes, it feels peaceful.”

A duck swims with her little ducklings.
They both smile.

The sun shines brighter.
The breeze moves the leaves.

Man says: “I like mornings like this.”
Woman says: “Me too.”
author: Ihor Karen
